itemLabel: Sir Wilfrid Lawson, 3rd Baronet, of Brayton

wikipedia_page.main: Sir Wilfrid Lawson, 3rd Baronet, of Brayton (21 October 1862 – 28 August 1937) was  an English Liberal politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1910 to 1916. He was also a keen sportsman who excelled at cricket and steeplechasing.
